@startuml filterLog
title Stock Movement Logs - Filter & Fetch Flow

actor User
participant "LogsPage.tsx" as Page
participant "useLogsList()" as Hook
participant "LogsFilters.tsx" as Filters
participant "toLogQueryParams()" as QueryBuilder
participant "apiFetch()" as ApiFetch
participant "GET /api/logs" as ApiRoute
participant "requireShopifySession()" as Auth
participant "listLogsFilterSchema\n(Zod)" as Schema
participant "listLogs()" as Service
participant "buildLogWhereQuery()" as WhereBuilder
participant "prismaEzoko\n.stockMovementLog" as Prisma
participant "StockMovementsTable" as Table

== Initialization ==

Page -> Hook: useLogsList()
Hook -> Hook: bootstrap via useEmbeddedBootstrap()
Hook --> Page: bootstrap.loading = true

note over Hook
    Waits for bootstrap to be ready
    (Shopify embedded session)
end note

Hook -> Hook: useEffect → bootstrap ready,\nnot initialized
Hook -> Hook: loadRows(EMPTY_LOG_FILTERS)
Hook -> Hook: setInitialized(true)

== Initial Load (empty filters) ==

Hook -> QueryBuilder: toLogQueryParams(EMPTY_LOG_FILTERS,\n"createdAt", "desc")
QueryBuilder --> Hook: "sortBy=createdAt&sortDirection=desc"

Hook -> ApiFetch: GET /api/logs?sortBy=createdAt&sortDirection=desc
ApiFetch -> ApiRoute: HTTP GET

ApiRoute -> Auth: requireShopifySession(request, {csrf:false
}
)
Auth --> ApiRoute: session OK

ApiRoute -> Schema: parseOrThrow(listLogsFilterSchema,\nsearchParams)
Schema --> ApiRoute: filters (sortBy=createdAt, sortDirection=desc)

ApiRoute -> Service: listLogs(filters)
Service -> WhereBuilder: buildLogWhereQuery(filters)
WhereBuilder --> Service: where = {}
(no active filters)

Service -> Prisma: findMany({ where:{}
    , orderBy:{createdAt:"desc"
}
, take:500
}
)
Prisma --> Service: StockMovementLog[]

Service -> Service: map → LogRow[]\n(dates as ISO strings)
Service --> ApiRoute: LogRow[]
ApiRoute --> ApiFetch: { logs: LogRow[] }
ApiFetch --> Hook: response.logs

Hook -> Hook: setRows(logs)\nsetLoading(false)
Hook --> Page: rows, loading=false

Page -> Table: <StockMovementsTable logs={rows} />
Table --> User: Table displayed

== Filter Interaction ==

User -> Filters: Edits a filter\n(activity / user / barcode /\nreferenceDoc / dateStart / dateEnd)
Filters -> Hook: onFiltersChange({ ...filters, [field]: value })
Hook -> Hook: setFilters(newFilters)
Filters --> User: UI updated (no request fired)

User -> Filters: Click "Apply filters"
Filters -> Hook: onApply() → loadRows()

Hook -> Hook: setLoading(true)\nsetError(null)
Hook -> QueryBuilder: toLogQueryParams(filters, "createdAt", "desc")

note over QueryBuilder
Only adds non-empty fields to params:
activity, user, dateStart, dateEnd,
barcode, referenceDoc + sortBy, sortDirection
end note

QueryBuilder --> Hook: query string

Hook -> ApiFetch: GET /api/logs?{
query string}
ApiFetch -> ApiRoute: HTTP GET

ApiRoute -> Auth: requireShopifySession(...)
Auth --> ApiRoute: session OK

ApiRoute -> Schema: parseOrThrow(listLogsFilterSchema, searchParams)
Schema --> ApiRoute: validated filters

ApiRoute -> Service: listLogs(filters)
Service -> WhereBuilder: buildLogWhereQuery(filters)

note over WhereBuilder
    For each active filter:
    • activity     → where.activity = value (exact match)
    • user         → contains, case-insensitive
    • barcode      → contains, case-insensitive
    • referenceDoc → contains, case-insensitive
    • dateStart/End → createdAt: { gte, lte }
    (parseDate with endOfDay for dateEnd)
end note

WhereBuilder --> Service: where {
    ... }
    Service -> Prisma: findMany({ where, orderBy:{
        createdAt:"desc"}, take:500 })
        Prisma --> Service: StockMovementLog[] (filtered)
        Service --> ApiRoute: LogRow[]
        ApiRoute --> ApiFetch: { logs: LogRow[] }
        ApiFetch --> Hook: response.logs
        Hook -> Hook: setRows(logs)\nsetLoading(false)
        Hook --> Page: rows updated
        Page -> Table: re-render with new logs
        Table --> User: Filtered table

        == Reset Filters ==

        User -> Filters: Click "Reset"
        note right: Button enabled only if\nhasActiveFilters = true
        Filters -> Hook: onReset() → resetFilters()
        Hook -> Hook: setFilters(EMPTY_LOG_FILTERS)
        Hook -> Hook: loadRows(EMPTY_LOG_FILTERS)
        note right of Hook: Fires immediately with empty filters\n(no re-render wait)

        Hook -> ApiFetch: GET /api/logs?sortBy=createdAt&sortDirection=desc
        ApiFetch -> ApiRoute: (same flow as initial load)
        ApiRoute --> Hook: all logs (max 500)
        Hook -> Hook: setRows(logs)\nsetLoading(false)
        Table --> User: Full table restored

        == Error Handling ==

        alt Network / server error
            ApiFetch --> Hook: throw Error
            Hook -> Hook: setError(message)\nsetLoading(false)
            Hook --> Page: error != null
            Page --> User: <s-banner tone="critical" error={...} />
        end

        @enduml
